article.headline: Texas-Pan American 72, N.J. Tech 60
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas (AP) -- Brian Burrell scored 25 points, including six 3-pointers, to help lead Texas-Pan American to a 72-60 victory over New Jersey Tech on Saturday. Burrell was 7-of-9 from the field and 5-of-6 from the free throw line. He also grabbed seven rebounds, matching Colin Lien for the team-high. Zach Trader came off the bench to add 14 points, while Paul Stoll had 13 points, 10 coming on free throws. The Broncs (12-10) led 35-23 at the break and turned 16 Highlander turnovers into 15 points. The difference could have come from the free throw line, where the Texas-Pan American made 80 percent compared to 57 percent by New Jersey Tech (3-18). Michael Manning came off the bench to lead the Highlanders with 13 points, including four 3-pointers. Marc Milbourne Swan had 11 bench points and Kraig Peters scored 10 points.
